res the face of patriarchy and gender-related violence in post-colonial Orissa. This volume will be of interest to students of history, social anthropology, political sociology and cultural studies, as well as those associated with non-governmental organisations and planners of public policy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aHISTORY / Asia / India & South Asia.2bisacsh  acolonialism.  aconversion.  aenvironment.  ahealth and medicine.  anationalism.  aoutcastes.  apopular movements.  apostcolonialism.  aprincely states.  atribals.1 aPati, Biswamoy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez9783111283630oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526130570423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526130570/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPc1986d2013